==English==

===Noun===
'''pimp''' (''plural:'' '''[[pimps]]''')
# One who provides gratification for the [[lust]] of others; a [[procurer]]; a [[pander]].
# (''slang, [[w:AAVE|AAVE]]'') Man who can easily attract women; a [[player]]/[[playa]].

====Translations====
*[[chulo]] (''[[w:Spanish language|Spanish]]'') {{m}}
*[[safado]] (''[[w:Portuguese language|Portuguese]]'') {{m}} 

===Verb (intransitive)===
'''pimp''' ([[pimps]], [[pimping]], [[pimped]])
# To procure women for the gratification of others' lusts; to [[pander]].
# (''Medical profession slang'') When the attending physician asks an impossible to answer question of a resident or medical student.
# (''US, [[w:AAVE|AAVE]]'') To excessively [[customise]] something, especially a vehicle, according to [[ghetto]] [[standard|standards]].
#:''You '''pimped''' out that [[Ac]] [[f'real]], [[dawg]].''

